{"key":"post-9977014","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9977014</id>\n<content>You can use any cereal grain, but you really should pressure cook the flour/verm mix if you do.&amp;nbsp; Brown rice flour is used because it can be steamed in a kettle, allowing new growers to get their feet wet without buying a pressure cooker.&amp;nbsp; I haven't yet seen a grain that outperforms brown rice in cakes, so you have nothing to gain by using oats or rye, etc., but if it's all you have, AND you have a pressure cooker, it's fine to use.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>9977009</prev>\n<first>9976985</first>\n<last>9977014</last>\n<when>1237154525</when>\n<utime>03/16/09 01:02 AM</utime>\n</post>"}